N2  - This paper addresses the problem commonly faced by R that is, the heuristic always found the optimal investment plan. In general, computational times were minimal when compared to data collection efforts, with the latter perhaps being the principal hurdle to full implementation. The sponsoring organization, however, felt that the unified approach offered by the methodology represented a major improvement over current analytic techniques.
